history.content: Thanks for bringing this up... this special titled was carried over from last year and does not reflect the enrollment process, as you have noticed.  Students have been and will be required to enroll in both secondary sections when signing up for the lecture.  I have removed this note from OSOC and no longer will appear tomorrow.
Thanks for bringing this up... looking into it now. Stay tuned for a more official response from our scheduler.

children.subject:
The number of lab sections is dependent on how many GSIs we can hire, but generally we find a way to increase the secondary sections if enrollment for these classes increases.

I have just added three new lab sections for EE40. They will appear on Telebears Monday AM.

Speaking of EE 40 enrollment, why is it that the number of seats for the discussion sections does not equal the number of seats for the lab sections? I wanted to enroll, but I could not enroll in a lab section because they were all full even though the discussion sections still had seats left.

history.content:
According to the Schedule of Classes, enrollment in EE 40 is subject to the following:

Students will not be able to enroll in the secondary discussion and lab sections via Tele-BEARS. Students can only register for the lecture. Labs and discussion sections will be decided during the first week of classes with student input. Attend the first lecture for lab and discussion section information.

However, I noticed that people have indeed been able to enroll in secondary sections via Tele-BEARS; for example, the schedule of classes lists DIS 101 as CURRENTLY FULL. Are students indeed allowed to enroll in secondary sections before classes start?
history.subject: EE 40 Enrollment: Secondary Sections
